Shell
(
Fig. 6H
; 
14A–C
; 
15A–C
). Length up to 
2.2 mm
; elongate­conic (SW/SL 0.39– 0.61, mean 0.50, n = 37); spire tall, straight to slightly convex in outline; last whorl evenly rounded or with subshoulder depression; suture simple or indented/impressed. Protoconch microsculpture uniform (
Fig. 6H
). Teleoconch up to 3.7 whorls in adult; aperture oval to pear­shaped; small, shorter than spire (AL/SL 0.30–0.45, mean 0.36, n = 37); outer lip orthocline to opisthocline; weakly thickened in adult, straight; posterior notch absent; inner lip thin and narrow, in partial contact or narrowly separated from parietal wall.
